[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    11[0m:[38;5;10m[49m This is the eighth recipe in Chapter 11 (Conversational AI / Virtual Assistants) and the chapter's first life-safety-critical patient-facing recipe. It is the chapter's first recipe to combine continuous-crisis-screening on every utterance as architectural primitive (not feature), companion-pattern avoidance as architectural discipline (recipe-distinct vs every prior chapter 11 bot), warm-handoff to licensed clinicians as primary safety architecture (vs alert-only patterns in 11.4 / 11.6 / 11.7), explicit non-therapist disclosure as architectural primitive (recipe-distinct), eligibility-check-and-off-ramp for excluded populations (psychotic-spectrum diagnoses, primary substance-use requiring specialized treatment, active inpatient or residential treatment, minors in adult-only deployments), patient-initiated default engagement to avoid surveillance flavor (recipe-distinct conservative engagement posture), bridge-and-stay-present pattern during crisis (recipe-distinct), per-state licensure coverage for the licensed-clinician workforce, separately-keyed sensitive-disclosure store with restricted access, separately-keyed crisis-event-record store, mental-health-specific privacy posture covering 42 CFR Part 2 for substance-use treatment information and state-specific mental-health-record statutes that exceed HIPAA baseline in many states, mandatory-reporting routing for child abuse / elder abuse / IPV / certain mental-health crisis types with state-specific variation, FDA-SaMD-strategy alignment for patient-facing mental-health software with therapeutic claims, and hybrid AI-plus-licensed-clinician deployment as the dominant evidence-based pattern.
