[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    13[0m:[38;5;10m[49m The opening Sam-at-11:47-PM-Wednesday vignette earns its position as the chapter's strongest single articulation of the activation-energy-when-the-thoughts-get-loud failure mode, with the safety-plan-in-the-drawer and the therapist-on-vacation and the medication-bottles-in-the-bathroom-drawer and the Priya-arrives-with-conversation-context-already-loaded as recipe-distinct grounding details. The "the activation energy required to open the drawer, find the notebook, read down the list, and start at step one is, in that moment, more than Sam has" framing, the "Sam knows this is a feature of the disease and not a personal failing" passage, and the "Sam is alive in the morning. This is a good outcome. It is not a typical outcome." pivot into the typical-outcome enumeration are the recipe's strongest single passage on the gap-between-what-the-population-needs-and-what-the-system-delivers primitive. The "the value is in three places: the consistency of crisis screening, the lower activation-energy access to evidence-based exercises, and the warm handoff infrastructure" framing earns its position as the recipe's clearest articulation of the why-the-bot-is-not-evaluated-on-engagement-metrics primitive.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    14[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    15[0m:[38;5;10m[49m The Technology section's "Why a Generic LLM Cannot Run a Mental-Health Support Bot" subsection's twelve-property enumeration is recipe-distinct and earns its position as the recipe's clearest articulation of the why-naked-LLM-in-front-of-mental-health-support-is-dangerous primitive. The companion-pattern-drift, the parasocial-companion-pattern-as-failure-mode, the no-theory-of-when-not-to-engage, the no-theory-of-mandatory-reporting, the no-theory-of-active-emergency, the no-theory-of-relationship-quality-boundaries, the harmful-coping-strategy-detection, and the state-specific-mental-health-privacy enumerations are the recipe's strongest single passage on the LLM-alone-is-not-a-product framing. The "What the Mental-Health Bot Has To Do That the Previous Bots Did Not" subsection's eight-structural-commitments enumeration (crisis screening as architectural primitive, therapeutic-content discipline with behavioral-health-clinical-leadership ownership, explicit non-therapist disclosure as architectural primitive, warm handoff to licensed clinicians as primary safety architecture, mandatory-reporting routing, companion-pattern avoidance as architectural discipline, mental-health-specific privacy and consent posture, FDA-strategy alignment) is the recipe's clearest articulation of the mental-health-bot-vs-other-chapter-11-bots-distinction primitive.
